        "content": "\n            <h1>Loop Challenges</h1>\n            <p>These challenges test your ability to use <code>for</code> and <code>while</code> loops effectively.</p>\n            \n            <h2>The Challenge:</h2>\n            <p>Print a \"number pyramid\". For example, if <code>n=3</code>, it should print:<br>\n            1<br>\n            2 2<br>\n            3 3 3</p>\n        \n<br><strong>Expected Output:</strong>\n<div class=\"code-block\" style=\"background: #1e1e2e; color: #a6accd; padding: 10px; margin-top: 5px; border-left: 3px solid #10b981; font-family: 'Fira Code', monospace; font-size: 0.9em;\">1\r<br>22\r<br>333\r<br>4444\r<br>55555</div>\n",
