        "content": "\n            <h1>Data Structure challenges</h1>\n            <p>Test your knowledge of lists, dictionaries, and sets.</p>\n            \n            <h2>The Challenge:</h2>\n            <p>Given a list <code>data = [1, 2, 2, 3, 4, 4, 5]</code>, create a new list with all <b>duplicates removed</b>. Hint: Use a <code>set()</code>.</p>\n        \n<br><strong>Expected Output:</strong>\n<div class=\"code-block\" style=\"background: #1e1e2e; color: #a6accd; padding: 10px; margin-top: 5px; border-left: 3px solid #10b981; font-family: 'Fira Code', monospace; font-size: 0.9em;\">Original: [1, 2, 2, 3, 4, 4, 5, 6, 6, 1]\r<br>Unique: [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6]</div>\n",
