    "19.5": {
        "title": "Level 5: Timed Logic",
        "content": "\n            <h1>Advanced Logic</h1>\n            <p>These challenges require combining multiple concepts like functions, loops, and conditions.</p>\n            \n            <h2>The Challenge:</h2>\n            <p>Write a function <code>is_prime(n)</code> that returns <code>True</code> if a number is prime, and <code>False</code> otherwise. A prime number is only divisible by 1 and itself.</p>\n        \n<br><strong>Expected Output:</strong>\n<div class=\"code-block\" style=\"background: #1e1e2e; color: #a6accd; padding: 10px; margin-top: 5px; border-left: 3px solid #10b981; font-family: 'Fira Code', monospace; font-size: 0.9em;\">Interactive Output (Depends on user input)</div>\n",
        "code": "# Write your Python code here\n",
        "solutionCode": "def is_prime(n):\n    if n < 2: return False\n    for i in range(2, int(n**0.5) + 1):\n        if n % i == 0:\n            return False\n    return True\n\nnum = int(input(\"Enter number to check: \"))\nprint(f\"Is {num} prime? {is_prime(num)}\")"
    }
